sus."},{"role":"Lawyer, partner","organization":"Lyman, Class & Co. (law firm)","location":"Montreal, Quebec, Canada","notes":"Admitted to practice law in the Province of Quebec; partner in Lyman, Class & Co. law firm. Distinct from Lyman Brothers drug firm."},{"role":"Superintendent of West Ward","organization":"Montreal City Council","location":"Montreal","notes":"Served on Montreal City Council as Superintendent of West Ward."},{"role":"Deacon","organization":"Congregational Church, Montreal","location":"Montreal"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"McGill graduate, Quebec lawyer, Lyman Brothers partner","body":"Henry Lyman graduated McGill College Montreal and studied further in England before being admitted to practice law in the Province of Quebec. He joined the family drug firm in 1829 at age fifteen and became a partner in Lyman Brothers — the largest pharmaceutical wholesaler in Canada — while also serving on Montreal City Council as Superintendent of West Ward and as Deacon in the Congregational Church."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three sons died young, four to old age","body":"Henry and Mary Corse Lyman had seven children together in Montreal between 1844 and 1861. Three died young: Arthur Ellis as an infant in 1847, Susan Alice at age five in 1853, and Roswell Corse at forty-two in 1892. The four surviving sons lived long lives, including Henry Herbert (who perished on the Empress of Ireland 1914) and Walter Ernest who reached eighty-nine."}],"slug":"henry-lyman-1813"},"X01252":{"id":"X01252","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":["canada_migration"],"sources":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD0583","date_year":1841,"date_month":8,"date_day":24,"l