91","X02825","I01230"],"notes":"Cimetière Mont-Royal (Mount Royal Cemetery), Outremont, Montreal QC. Major Protestant cemetery founded 1852 on the slopes of Mount Royal. Burial site of multiple members of the Lyman family — Hannah Stiles Lyman's descendants who became prominent Montreal druggists, lawyers, and civic figures: Elisha Lyman Jr. (with his three wives memorialized together), Henry Lyman, Mary Corse Lyman, Henry Herbert Lyman (later commemorated here after death on the Empress of Ireland 1914), Albert Clarence Lyman, Frederick Stiles Lyman, Edith Mary Louise Lyman, and others."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}